title: Ottawa Comiccon 2022 (Official)
Description: * En fran√ßais, d√©filer vers le bas*Ottawa Comiccon is a pop-culture fan convention that showcases artists and products from entertainment genres like: Sci-fi, Horror, Anime, Gaming in all its forms, and, of course, bande dessin√©e and comic books. It features a large array of exhibits with several companies demonstrating their wares and a few vehicles or set pieces from film or television are on display, a shopping experience like no other, aimed at fans that are looking for games, T-Shirts, comics, toys, statues, replicas and more collector items.Fans have the opportunity come to meet their favorite creators from the world of comics get their autographs, buy a sketch or thank them for their work. Additionally, one of the biggest draws, fans get to meet the personalities behind their favorite TV shows and movies. Celebrities participate in autograph sessions, photo opportunities and stage appearances that accommodate between 300 and 2000 fans.Fans are encouraged (but not obliged) to come dressed as their favourite pop culture characters, be they from movies, TV, video games or comics. It culminates at the Masquerade, the big costuming competition that brings in judges from across the globe, over 50 competitors, and close to 2000 fans to cheer them on when they hit the big stage.Over the course of three days, fans are treated to over 50 different panel discussions and workshops that help further promote comics, costuming, gaming and pop culture in general.*En fran√ßais*Le Comiccon d'Ottawa est un √©v√©nement destin√© aux amateurs de culture populaire √† l‚Äôoccasion duquel ces derniers ont la chance de rencontrer des artistes et de voir un large √©ventail de produits issus de l‚Äôunivers du divertissement : science-fiction, horreur, anime, jeux vid√©o sous toutes leurs formes et, bien s√ªr, bandes dessin√©es et comic books. On y trouve une grande diversit√© d‚Äôexposants, notamment des entreprises qui y pr√©sentent leurs marchandises, ainsi que des v√©hicules ou d‚Äôautres √©l√©ments marquants de films ou de s√©ries t√©l√©vis√©es. Il s‚Äôagit d‚Äôune occasion unique pour les collectionneurs de trouver le tee-shirt, le comic book, le jouet, la figurine, ou la r√©plique dont ils r√™vent.Les aficionados de comic books et de bandes dessin√©es ont quant √† eux la chance de rencontrer leurs artistes pr√©f√©r√©s, de demander leur autographe, d‚Äôacheter un dessin ou de les remercier pour leur travail. L‚Äôun des points marquants de l‚Äô√©v√©nement est certes la possibilit√© pour les visiteurs de rencontrer les artisans m√™mes de leur √©mission de t√©l√© ou de leur film pr√©f√©r√©. Les vedettes participent √† des s√©ances de photo et de signature d‚Äôautographes, et donnent des conf√©rences accueillant de 300 √† 2 000 personnes.On encourage les visiteurs (sans les obliger, toutefois) √† se costumer sous les traits de leur ic√¥ne de la culture populaire pr√©f√©r√©e (cin√©ma, t√©l√©, jeu vid√©o ou comic book, par exemple). Le d√©fil√© de costumes atteint son apog√©e lors de la mascarade, grand concours de costumes pr√©sid√© par des juges venus des quatre coins du monde qui notent plus de 40 concurrents devant les encouragements de pr√®s de 2 000 amateurs r√©unis pour l‚Äôoccasion.Pendant les trois jours de l‚Äô√©v√©nement, les visiteurs sont invit√©s √† plus de 50 groupes de discussion et ateliers visant la promotion des comic books, des costumes, des jeux vid√©o et de la culture populaire en g√©n√©ral.

title: Afrofest Ottawa 2021
Description: AfroFest Ottawa is a free, yearly Music and Arts festival that showcases the best of African culture and entertainment in the nation‚Äôs Capital.This festival gives all Canadians a chance to experience the beauty and wonder of African culture and expression. It promotes a sense of integration and representation for African Canadians, and celebrates a culture that is often misunderstood or undervalued.This festival highlights local artists who struggle to find opportunities to showcase themselves in the Ottawa music scene, and provides artisans of African fashion, goods and crafts with a chance to display their wares.There is also a place for authentic African cuisine food vendors and restaurants to promote their businesses, sample and sell their food.With live performances from both local and international artists, children's activities and fashion shows, this is a festival the whole family can enjoy.Last year was our first edition and because of the restrictions due to COVID-19, we had to produce an online festival.This year, we are happy to announce that we will be hosting a in person festival at our well known beach in OTTAWA "Mooney's Bay" on September 4TH and 5TH.Come have fun while discovering local talents and diverse African culture at our free festival.THIS IS A FREE FESTIVAL BUT PLEASE WATCH OUT FOR THE FREE TICKET LINK SO YOU CAN YOUR FREE TICKET TO THE FESTIVAL!!PS: If for any reason, social gathering ca

title: Ottawa & District Labour Council
Description: 5 FilmsDo Nothing And Do it WellThe true story of Melbourne's radical Chinese cabinetmakers whose militant union defied racial stereotypes and struck fear into the White Australian establishment.Treaty Walk - A Journey for Common GroundThe film follows a group of Indigenous elders, Healthcare Workers, and others as they embark on a two week long walking journey from Edmonton, Alberta/Treaty 6 Territory to Calgary, Alberta/Treaty 7 Territory to explore together what it means to be treaty people, working and living on common ground.Mixi"CHAKKI"ÔøΩ ('MIXI' in English/ 'MIXEUR' in french) is an UNRELEASED film entirely made using "SEEDS". Real PULSES & GRAMS & SPROUTS were used in motion to create scenarios as a metaphorical representation of GROWTH & FUTURE of a nation and shows the "DARK REALITY" behind your favourite DISH.A Highrise Laundry Room Within the laundry room's common space, six housekeeper gradually share their own highly personal stories.People Show1 38: Last dayA short dreamlike drama about power, loss and loyalty. People Show 138: Last Day, follows HR manager Sidney, who after thirty years of working at an industrial sock factory faces a challenging dilemma that could affect the livelihood of his employees.

title: Virtual Ottawa Centre Group
Description: VIRTUAL MEETING - ONLINE ONLY at our regular date/time of 7 PM on the 2nd Tuesday of the month.Meeting For: Everyone welcome: parents and supportersEmail lllc.ottawacentre@gmail.com for meeting joining details.You are always welcome to attend LLLC meetings before and after you have welcomed your baby. Bring your breastfeeding/chestfeeding questions and concerns, talk about your joys and challenges or come and just listen. Babies and young children are always welcome, All La Leche League Canada Leaders are volunteers. They are experienced breastfeeding/chestfeeding parents who have been accredited to provide up-to-date breastfeeding/chestfeeding information, encouragement and support.

title: Ottawa Santa Shuffle 2021
Description: Every year, Santa Shuffle brings passionate individuals from across the country to support vulnerable Canadians and the work of The Salvation Army.This year will be no exception. We are excited to announce that Santa Shuffle will be staying virtual this year to bring everyone together for a meaningful, fun and safe 5 K fun run or 1K elf walk between December 4th to 5th, 2021. Funds will go to The Salvation Army Bethany Hope Centre programs and services for young parent families.Don‚Äôt forget to dress up in your  Christmas outfit for your run/walk and spread the joy and festivities of the season with your community online using #santashuffleottRegister Today at www.santashuffle.ca Stay tuned for more details about social media contests this year including Best Dressed competitions for individuals, groups and pets! You can learn more about this year's contests at https://www.santashuffle.ca/awards/

title: OTTAWA: Decent work organizing meeting
Description: Let's get organized in Ottawa to fight for: - A $20 minimum wage; - At least 10 employer-provided paid sick days; - Equal pay for part-time, contract & temp agency workers; - An end to misclassification and real protections for gig workers; and - So much more!  We'll meet online using Zoom to plan out next steps. Don't forget to RSVP to receive the Zoom link:https://www.justice4workers.org/ottawa_decent_work_organizing_meeting_nov23See you there!

title: Ottawa Free Virtual Zoom + Twitch Party
Description: Online Virtual Party | Zoom + Twitch @ Club Virtual | Sat Aug 1---Refer to your city times at the bottom---Club Virtual provides a FREE virtual Zoom party space for everyone to join with other party goers experiencing a high energy, engaging and lighthearted pleasure. We also have our DJs live streaming a mix of Mainstream, Club Anthems, EDM/House, Hip Hop & Reggaeton music on our Twitch!The Concept is Simple:‚Ä¢ Participants will be able to access the virtual party with their webcams through our private Zoom Room, while we live stream our DJ through Twitch at www.twitch.tv/insideclubvirtual ‚Ä¢ Everyone will see everyone on Zoom. You will have the ability to engage in messages & mingle with others on both Zoom/Twitch! Zoom will be muted with no sound, for sound you listen to our DJ on Twitch.‚Ä¢ You recreate a nightclub at home: Wear your best outfits! Light up your room: blacklights, Christmas lights, etc. Make yourself a drink & get ready to party!‚Ä¢ Be prepared for fun contests & challenges throughout the night on Zoom. Time to shine! Show your best dance moves to thousands of participants!Tickets for our private Zoom room & Twitch Stream will be FREE as long as you register for your free pass! Follow us on instagram @insideclubvirtualWe are accepting donations to help us continue doing FREE events for everyone instead of ticketed. So please donate whatever you can, be it $1, $2, $5, less or more. (Donations will help us cover costs to keep these events free)CLICK THE LINK TO RESERVE YOUR FREE TICKETS & FOR DONATIONS. title: Odd Creatures of Ottawa with Rebecca Lewis
Description: Online via Zoom - Registration RequiredExplore some of the unexpected wildlife of the Ottawa Refuge, and some that have unexpected or just plain weird adaptations and features. Who wouldn't love a bird shaped like a potato that, I have heard, tastes like liver? Rebecca Lewis is the Visitor Services Specialist for Ottawa National Wildlife Refuge. She has worked at the refuge since 1996 and has been with the Service since 1990. A graduate of the University of Wisconsin-Stevens Point, she began her career as a Co-op Student with the Litchfield Wetland Management District in Minnesota. She discovered her love of visitor services while working at the Seney National Wildlife Refuge in Michigan. Some of her favorite aspects of her job have been working with the Federal Junior Duck Stamp Program, sharing her love of birds with many visitors to the refuge, and the many volunteers she has had the pleasure to work with over the years. Lewis is originally from Wisconsin and has always enjoyed spending time outdoors. Rebecca has two teenagers, a son and a daughter, who are active in band, drama, writing, Girl Scouts and cosplay. She enjoys birding, traveling, her two teenagers, volunteering and time with family and friends.This program is free but donations may be made online to support the Friends of Ottawa National Wildlife Refuge: Donate Now at https://friendsofottawanwr.networkforgood.com/projects/104514-support-the-conservation-of-ottawa-national-wildlife-refugeMore info: https://www.friendsofottawanwr.org/events.html

title: Kitchissippi-Ottawa Valley Chapter Launch Meeting
Description: The Council of Canadians announces the Public Launch of its new Kitchissippi-Ottawa Valley Chapter. Valley residents are invited to attend. Due to COVID public health concerns, this event will be held on Zoom, on October 28, 2021, beginning at 6:30 PM. You get a session link with this ZOOM Registration:<https://us02web.zoom.us/meeting/register/tZYsdeCsrj0uE9ZLabTehcv3WHlx8DbCTRLa>The agenda for this evening includes:  *** An introduction to the Council of Canadians and how it can support good social and environmental change in a rural region like ours.***  Brief presentations on upcoming chapter plans including a FUN approach to climate action education and initiating a youth art exhibit for Earth Day. *** Discussion of community participants' questions and concerns. For more than 3 decades, the Council of Canadians has been a public activist champion for clean fresh water, climate action, public health care, and vibrant democracy in Canada, as well as many other environmental, social and economic issues. The Council is non-partisan and financed only through member-support, so we can speak freely on issues that concern us.VISIT OUR WEBSITE TO LEARN MORE ABOUT OUR NEW CHAPTER:https://kovcouncil.wordpress.com/Some county residents may have already heard about this chapter.  After a handful of Renfrew County residents came together a few months ago to form this new chapter, the group has already been active on climate issues, pollinator-friendly policies, in solidarity with the Algonquin Anishinabeg for justice about residential schools operations, and other concerns.The Council invites Renfrew County neighbours and allies to attend this launch and share about the issues that are crucial for you. Climate chaos weather? Wildlife habitat and wetland protection? Sustainable forestry? Pharmacare? Rural public transport? Political accountability and transparency? Clean drinking water? Or something else?We hope you will spend 90 minutes of your evening on October 28th to check us out, starting at 6:30 PM.Can‚Äôt attend or have questions?Email us: kitchissippiottawacocchapter@gmail.com Hope to see you soon,Ann, Dan, Diane, Duncan, Ian, and Kathy
